structured.title: Critique Of Charismatic Prophets And Fake Miracles
structured.overview: The speaker delivers a detailed, angry critique of prominent charismatic Christian leaders and prophetic figures, calling many of them frauds and exposing what he sees as systematic fakery in the movement. He analyzes specific prophetic moments by Sean Bowles (Boles), including an incident involving a woman named Kelly Rhodes and her mother Doris, and another involving Chris Gore‚Äôs disabled daughter Charlotte at Bethel Church. By comparing Bowles‚Äô public prophecies to easily accessible information from Facebook and websites, he argues that the supposed supernatural knowledge (birthdays, names, dog‚Äôs name, address-like ‚Äò1 0 5 Slaughterhouse‚Äô) was actually pulled from online sources rather than revealed by God. He emphasizes his concern for vulnerable believers manipulated by such leaders, criticizes revival culture for enabling fakers, and urges good charismatic leaders to publicly call out corrupt figures despite legal and reputational risks. The monologue includes references to past whistleblowing efforts, the removal of a Bethel video after he asked questions, and the continuing disability of Charlotte as evidence that the ‚Äúfull healing‚Äù prophecy did not come to pass.

## Critique of Charismatic Leadership & Culture  
- Claims many charismatic leaders are long-term fakers, frauds  
- Names cited as fakers: Paul Cain, Bob Jones, Mike Bickle, William Branham  
- Argues ‚Äúcover-up culture‚Äù protects leaders, devastates congregations  

## God‚Äôs Generals & Systemic Issues  
- Book ‚ÄúGod‚Äôs Generals‚Äù said to include multiple frauds  
- Bill Johnson reportedly recommended that book  
- Emphasis: not all charismatics bad, but system protects abusers  

## Sean Bolz: Doris Rhodes / Slaughterhouse 105  
- Sean gives word to Kelly, focuses on mom ‚ÄúDoris Rhodes‚Äù  
- Tries to call out ‚ÄúPsalm 105‚Ä¶ slaughterhouse‚Ä¶ 105 something‚Äù  
- Research found real ‚ÄúDoris Rhodes‚Äù at 105 Slaughterhouse, wrong person  

## Evidence of Cold Reading / Data Mining  
- Presenter calls ‚Äú105 Slaughterhouse‚Äù a smoking gun  
- Says no way random prophetic hit wrong Doris with real address  
- States he personally verified Doris/Slaughterhouse data via screenshot  

## Risk in Calling Out Abuse  
- Speaker consulted lawyers before exposing named leaders  
- Notes personal risk but says leaders must take similar risks  
- Urges good leaders: prove it by publicly calling out known fakers  

## Sean Bolz: Charlotte Gore at Bethel  
- Sean ‚Äúcalls out‚Äù Charlotte Gore, Oct 7 birthday, very disabled  
- Prophesies ‚Äúfull healing,‚Äù parents‚Äô prayers ‚Äúare working‚Äù  
- Uses word over Charlotte as picture of Bethel‚Äôs long-term issues resolving  

## Bethel Context & Leadership Presence  
- Word given at Bethel, with Bill/Benny Johnson, Danny Silk present  
- Bethel narrative: always increasing miracles, upward revival trajectory  
- Sean positioned as gateway to even greater miracles and healings  

## Online Info Matching the Prophecy  
- Chris Gore: Bethel healing director, 3 daughters, disabled Charlotte  
- Family photo with three girls and dog ‚ÄúMaverick‚Äù posted online  
- Sean references Maverick; all info easily available via Facebook/website  

## Aftermath & Current Situation  
- Video reportedly removed after speaker privately contacted Chris Gore  
- 2014 post: Chris celebrates word, sees it for wider body  
- 2024 photo: Charlotte still clearly disabled, prophecy unfulfilled  

## Next Steps  
- Reassess trust in prophetic figures using verifiable evidence  
- Church leaders: investigate, publicly confront known manipulation  
- Individuals: fact-check public prophetic claims, especially specific details
